For Loop + If / If-Else Practice Questions

Print all even numbers from 1 to 50.

Print all numbers divisible by 3 from 1 to 100.

Print numbers from 1 to 20 and mark them as “Even” or “Odd”.

Print all numbers from 1 to 50 and indicate if they are divisible by 5.

Print all vowels from a given string.

Count the number of positive and negative numbers in a list.

Print all numbers from 1 to 50, but replace multiples of 3 with "Fizz" and multiples of 5 with "Buzz" (FizzBuzz).

Print squares of all numbers from 1 to 20 that are greater than 10.

From a list of ages, print “Minor” if age < 18, else “Adult”.

Print numbers 1–30 and label them as “Prime” or “Not Prime”.


While Loop + If / If-Else Practice Questions

Keep asking the user to enter a password until the correct one is entered.

Generate numbers from 1 to 20 using a while loop and print “Even” or “Odd” for each.

Keep taking input from the user until they enter a number divisible by 7.

Simulate a simple menu-driven program (1. Deposit, 2. Withdraw, 3. Exit) using while loop and if-elif-else.


Combined Logic

Create a number guessing game: keep asking the user until they guess the secret number, and give hints “Too high” or “Too low”.

From a list of numbers, print all numbers greater than 50 and indicate whether each is even or odd.

Print multiplication table for a number entered by the user, but label multiples of 2 as “Even” and multiples of 3 as “Divisible by 3”.

Ask the user to enter 5 words. Print each word and indicate if it has more vowels or consonants.

Create a simple “quiz game”: ask 3 questions, keep score, and give a final message based on the score (pass/fail).
